title: Wreckage of Indonesia jet spotted
text:
Wreckage of Indonesia jet spotted 17 August 2015 Save 
The wreckage of an Indonesian plane, which went missing with 54 people onboard, has been located. 
According to the BBC , local officials have located the Trigana Air flight in the remote western Papua region. 
The plane was en route from the provincial capital, Jayapura, to the town of Oksibil. 
It is not known whether any of the 44 adult passengers, five children and infants, and five crew survived. 
The BBC also reported that the plane was carrying Â£300,000 worth of local currency for villagers living in the region.
